Virginia Tech, a renowned technical university, offers degrees in computer science, agriculture, engineering, and business.
Founded in 1872 as a land-grant school, it focuses on research in biotechnology, energy, and fuel-cell technology.
The campus was rocked by a tragic shooting incident, resulting in the deaths of 32 individuals.
President George W. Bush attended a memorial service to honor the victims.
Classes were canceled for the week as the community mourned the senseless loss.
The nation grieved alongside Virginia Tech, recognizing the day as one of profound sadness.
